APPENDIX.

A tenant's homage.

The following memorandum is written in a hand of the fifteenth century on a blank space of sol. 163b:

Whan a tenant shal do his homage he shal holde his handys togidir, and put them in his lordys handys, And shal sey in this sorme that solwith: Ι becom your man fro this day sorward sor tho londes that 1 hold οΙ you, And trew feyth shal bere to you ageyns al persones that may leve, by knythis seruice‚ savyng the feyth that I ovh (owe) to the kyng and odyr that Ι have don homage to.
